<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>Eval report — {{ current.run_id }} [{{ status_label }}]</title>
<style>
  :root {
    --surface: #fcfcfb; --plane: #f4f4f1; --card: #ffffff;
    --ink: #0b0b0b; --ink-2: #52514e; --muted: #898781;
    --grid: #e1e0d9; --axis: #c3c2b7; --border: rgba(11,11,11,0.10);
    --series: #2a78d6; --area: rgba(42,120,214,0.10);
    --good: #0ca30c; --warning: #fab219; --critical: #d03b3b;
    --good-ink: #006300; --crit-ink: #b31d1d;
    --old: rgba(208,59,59,0.09); --new: rgba(12,163,12,0.10);
  }
  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    :root {
      --surface: #1a1a19; --plane: #0d0d0d; --card: #222220;
      --ink: #ffffff; --ink-2: #c3c2b7; --muted: #898781;
      --grid: #2c2c2a; --axis: #383835; --border: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
      --series: #3987e5; --area: rgba(57,135,229,0.14);
      --good: #0ca30c; --warning: #fab219; --critical: #e05a5a;
      --good-ink: #35c635; --crit-ink: #ef8a8a;
      --old: rgba(224,90,90,0.14); --new: rgba(12,163,12,0.16);
    }
  }
  * { box-sizing: border-box; }
  body {
    margin: 0; padding: 2rem 1rem; background: var(--plane); color: var(--ink);
    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", sans-serif; line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .wrap { max-width: 940px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .card {
    background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.4rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  h1 { font-size: 1.5rem; margin: 0 0 .2rem; }
  h2 { font-size: 1.05rem; margin: 0 0 .9rem; letter-spacing: .01em; }
  .sub { color: var(--ink-2); margin: 0; font-size: .95rem; }
  .explain { color: var(--ink-2); font-size: .9rem; background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; padding: .7rem .9rem; margin: 0; }
  .explain strong { color: var(--ink); }

  /* verdict banner */
  .verdict { display: flex; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-start;
    border-left: 6px solid var(--muted); }
  .verdict.ok { border-color: var(--good); }
  .verdict.warning { border-color: var(--warning); }
  .verdict.critical { border-color: var(--critical); }
  .verdict.baseline { border-color: var(--series); }
  .badge { flex: none; width: 46px; height: 46px; border-radius: 50%;
    display: grid; place-items: center; font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 700;
    color: #fff; }
  .ok .badge { background: var(--good); }
  .warning .badge { background: var(--warning); color: #3a2a00; }
  .critical .badge { background: var(--critical); }
  .baseline .badge { background: var(--series); }
  .verdict h1 { font-size: 1.3rem; }

  /* KPI tiles */
  .tiles { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(140px, 1fr));
    gap: .8rem; }
  .tile { background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px; padding: .8rem .9rem; }
  .tile .k { color: var(--muted); font-size: .72rem; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .06em; margin: 0 0 .35rem; }
  .tile .v { font-size: 1.7rem; font-weight: 650; margin: 0;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  .tile .d { font-size: .82rem; margin: .2rem 0 0; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  .up { color: var(--good-ink); } .down { color: var(--crit-ink); }

  /* category bars */
  .catrow { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 84px 1fr 96px; align-items: center;
    gap: .6rem; margin: .45rem 0; }
  .catrow .name { color: var(--ink-2); font-size: .88rem; text-transform: capitalize; }
  .bar { background: var(--grid); border-radius: 5px; height: 12px; overflow: hidden; }
  .bar > span { display: block; height: 100%; background: var(--series); border-radius: 5px; }
  .catrow .val { text-align: right; font-size: .85rem; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }

  /* trend chart */
  svg.trend { width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }
  .trend .grid { stroke: var(--grid); stroke-width: 1; }
  .trend .axis { fill: var(--muted); font-size: 11px; }
  .trend .area { fill: var(--area); stroke: none; }
  .trend .line { fill: none; stroke: var(--series); stroke-width: 2.5;
    stroke-linejoin: round; stroke-linecap: round; }
  .trend .dot { fill: var(--series); }
  .trend .dot-last { fill: var(--series); stroke: var(--card); stroke-width: 2; }
  .trend .pointlbl { fill: var(--ink); font-size: 12px; font-weight: 650; }
  .empty { color: var(--muted); font-size: .9rem; }

  /* tables */
  table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; font-size: .88rem; }
  th, td { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: .55rem .6rem;
    text-align: left; vertical-align: top; }
  th { color: var(--muted); font-size: .72rem; text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: .05em; font-weight: 600; }
  td.old { background: var(--old); } td.new { background: var(--new); }
  .cat-tag { font-weight: 650; }
  .arrow { color: var(--muted); }
  ul.imp { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.1rem; color: var(--ink-2); font-size: .9rem; }

  .pill { display: inline-block; font-size: .72rem; padding: .1rem .5rem;
    border-radius: 20px; border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--ink-2);
    background: var(--surface); }
  .drift { border-left: 6px solid var(--warning); }
  .meta { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: .4rem .6rem; color: var(--ink-2);
    font-size: .82rem; }
  footer { color: var(--muted); font-size: .78rem; text-align: center;
    margin-top: 1.4rem; }
  .legend { color: var(--muted); font-size: .8rem; margin: .2rem 0 0; }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrap">

  <div class="card">
    <h1>AI Classifier — Quality Report</h1>
    <p class="sub">Automated regression check for a customer-support email classifier.</p>
    <p class="explain" style="margin-top:.8rem">
      <strong>What am I looking at?</strong> An AI reads support emails and sorts them
      into <em>billing / technical / account / general</em>. Every prompt or model
      change is tested against {{ total }} human-graded emails. This page compares the
      latest test to the previous one and flags any drop in quality — the same check
      that runs automatically on every pull request.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="card verdict {{ status }}">
    <div class="badge">{{ status_icon }}</div>
    <div>
      <h1>{{ headline }}</h1>
      <p class="sub">{{ explanation }}</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  {% if drift_detected %}
  <div class="card drift">
    <h2 style="margin-bottom:.3rem">⚠ Slow-drift warning</h2>
    <p class="sub">The rolling average pass rate over recent runs is
      {{ "%.1f%%"|format(drift_avg_pct) }} — trending down over time even if no single
      run tripped the alert. This catches gradual decay that per-run checks miss.</p>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Scorecard</h2>
    <div class="tiles">
      <div class="tile">
        <p class="k">Pass rate</p>
        <p class="v">{{ "%.0f%%"|format(pass_pct) }}</p>
        {% if delta_pct is not none %}
        <p class="d {{ 'up' if delta_pct >= 0 else 'down' }}">
          {{ "%+.1f%%"|format(delta_pct) }} vs previous
          ({{ "%.0f%%"|format(baseline_pct) }})</p>
        {% else %}<p class="d" style="color:var(--muted)">baseline</p>{% endif %}
      </div>
      <div class="tile">
        <p class="k">Cases passed</p>
        <p class="v">{{ passed }}<span style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--muted)">/{{ total }}</span></p>
        {% if errored %}<p class="d down">{{ errored }} errored (e.g. rate limit)</p>
        {% else %}<p class="d" style="color:var(--muted)">no errors</p>{% endif %}
      </div>
      <div class="tile">
        <p class="k">Regressions</p>
        <p class="v {{ 'down' if regression_count else '' }}">{{ regression_count }}</p>
        <p class="d" style="color:var(--muted)">passed before, fail now</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tile">
        <p class="k">Improvements</p>
        <p class="v {{ 'up' if improvement_count else '' }}">{{ improvement_count }}</p>
        <p class="d" style="color:var(--muted)">failed before, pass now</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tile">
        <p class="k">Summary quality</p>
        <p class="v">{{ "%.2f"|format(current.avg_judge_score) if current.avg_judge_score is not none else "n/a" }}<span style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--muted)">/5</span></p>
        <p class="d" style="color:var(--muted)">LLM-judged relevance</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tile">
        <p class="k">Avg latency</p>
        <p class="v">{{ "%.0f"|format(current.avg_latency_ms) }}<span style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--muted)">ms</span></p>
        <p class="d" style="color:var(--muted)">{{ current.total_tokens }} tokens total</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="legend">Verdict thresholds: a pass-rate drop over
      {{ "%.0f%%"|format(warning_pct) }} is a warning, over
      {{ "%.0f%%"|format(critical_pct) }} is critical and blocks the merge.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Accuracy by category</h2>
    {% for c in categories %}
    <div class="catrow">
      <span class="name">{{ c.name }}</span>
      <span class="bar"><span style="width: {{ "%.0f"|format(c.acc * 100) }}%"></span></span>
      <span class="val">{{ "%.0f%%"|format(c.acc * 100) }}{% if c.delta is not none and c.delta != 0 %}
        <span class="{{ 'up' if c.delta > 0 else 'down' }}">({{ "%+.0f"|format(c.delta * 100) }})</span>{% endif %}</span>
    </div>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

  {% if diff and diff.regressions %}
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Regressed cases — {{ diff.regressions | length }}</h2>
    <p class="legend" style="margin-bottom:.6rem">These emails were classified
      correctly before and are wrong now. <span class="pill" style="background:var(--old)">left = before</span>
      <span class="pill" style="background:var(--new)">right = after</span></p>
    <div style="overflow-x:auto">
    <table>
      <tr><th>Email (excerpt)</th><th>Should be</th><th>Before</th><th>After</th></tr>
      {% for f in diff.regressions %}
      <tr>
        <td>{{ f.input[:120] }}{% if f.input|length > 120 %}…{% endif %}</td>
        <td><span class="cat-tag">{{ f.expected_category.value }}</span></td>
        <td class="old">{% if f.baseline_output %}<span class="cat-tag">{{ f.baseline_output.category.value }}</span>{% else %}<em>error</em>{% endif %}</td>
        <td class="new">{% if f.current_output %}<span class="cat-tag">{{ f.current_output.category.value }}</span>{% else %}<em>error</em>{% endif %}</td>
      </tr>
      {% endfor %}
    </table>
    </div>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  {% if diff and diff.improvements %}
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Improved cases — {{ diff.improvements | length }}</h2>
    <ul class="imp">
      {% for f in diff.improvements %}
      <li>{{ f.input[:90] }}{% if f.input|length > 90 %}…{% endif %} —
        now <strong>{{ f.current_output.category.value if f.current_output else "error" }}</strong>
        <span class="arrow">(target: {{ f.expected_category.value }})</span></li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Pass-rate trend — last {{ n_runs }} run(s)</h2>
    {{ trend_svg | safe }}
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <h2>Run details</h2>
    <div class="meta">
      <span class="pill">run {{ current.run_id }}</span>
      <span class="pill">prompt {{ current.prompt_version }}</span>
      <span class="pill">model {{ current.model }}</span>
      <span class="pill">{{ current.timestamp.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M UTC") }}</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <footer>Generated by regression-detector · {{ current.run_id }}</footer>
</div>
</body>
</html>
